&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; I forgot to mention that I used a combination of the code in the
&gt; selftest package and in the Heritrix webapp to figure out the relevant
&gt; sequence of calls.
&gt; 
&gt; X.
&gt; --- In archive-crawler@yahoogroups.com 
&gt; &lt;mailto:archive-crawler%40yahoogroups.com&gt;, &quot;xavier_sautejeau&quot;
&gt; &lt;xvrstj-registration@...&gt; wrote:
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; Hi,
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; I&#39;ve tried something similar (integrating Heritrix with a Tomcat
&gt;  &gt; Webapp) and succeeded to a point. Unfortunately I wanted to use the
&gt;  &gt; MirrorWriter instead of the ArcWriter and was not able to use it with
&gt;  &gt; Heritrix 2.0. I therefore reverted to 1.12.
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; Anyhow, here are the relevant excerpts of my code, hope this helps :
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; --------------------------
&gt;  &gt; import org.archive.crawler.Heritrix;
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; import org.archive.crawler.framework.JobStage;
&gt;  &gt; import org.archive.util.JmxWaiter;
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; import java.io.*;
&gt;  &gt; import java.util.Set;
&gt;  &gt; import java.lang.management.ManagementFactory;
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; import javax.management.MBeanServer;
&gt;  &gt; import javax.management.ObjectName;
&gt;  &gt; import javax.servlet.*;
&gt;  &gt; import javax.servlet.http.*;
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; import coreservlets.ServletUtilities;
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; /**
&gt;  &gt; * Heritrix 2.0 Tentative Integration
&gt;  &gt; */
&gt;  &gt; public class HeritrixControl extends HttpServlet {
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; final static String HERITRIX_HOME = System.getenv(&quot;HERITRIX_HOME&quot;);
&gt;  &gt; final static String JAVA_LANG_STRING = &quot;java.lang.String&quot;;
&gt;  &gt; final static String JAVA_LANG_INTEGER = &quot;java.lang.Integer&quot;;
&gt;  &gt; private boolean started = false;
&gt;  &gt; private ObjectName engine = null;
&gt;  &gt; private MBeanServer server = null;
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; public void doPost(HttpServletRequest request,
&gt;  &gt; HttpServletResponse response)
&gt;  &gt; throws ServletException, IOException {
&gt;  &gt; doGet(request, response);
&gt;  &gt; }
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; protected void startHeritrix() {
&gt;  &gt; try {
&gt;  &gt; String[] args = {
&gt;  &gt; &quot;-b&quot;, &quot;localhost&quot;,
&gt;  &gt; &quot;-p&quot;, &quot;8100&quot;,
&gt;  &gt; //&quot;-a&quot;,&quot;LOGIN:PASSWORD&quot;,
&gt;  &gt; &quot;-n&quot;, // no WEBUI
&gt;  &gt; //&quot;-r&quot;, &quot;profile-basic_seed_sites&quot;};
&gt;  &gt; &quot;-j&quot;, HERITRIX_HOME + &quot;/jobs&quot;};
&gt;  &gt; Heritrix.main(args);
&gt;  &gt; // with Tomcat and Heritrix, we always get such an exception
&gt;  &gt; } catch (javax.naming.OperationNotSupportedException e) {
&gt;  &gt; } catch (Exception e) {
&gt;  &gt; }
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; try {
&gt;  &gt; engine = lazyGetEngine();
&gt;  &gt; server = ManagementFactory.getPlatformMBeanServer();
&gt;  &gt; this.waitForCrawlFinish();
&gt;  &gt; } catch (Exception e) {
&gt;  &gt; }
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; }
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; protected void stopHeritrix() {
&gt;  &gt; try {
&gt;  &gt; engine =lazyGetEngine();
&gt;  &gt; server = ManagementFactory.getPlatformMBeanServer();
&gt;  &gt; server.invoke(engine, &quot;close&quot;, new Object[0], new String[0]);
&gt;  &gt; engine = null;
&gt;  &gt; server = null;
&gt;  &gt; } catch (Exception e) {
&gt;  &gt; }
&gt;  &gt; }
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; protected void waitForCrawlFinish() throws Exception {
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; // Above invocation should have created a new SheetManager and a new
&gt;  &gt; // CrawlController for the job. Find the CrawlController.
&gt;  &gt; ObjectName crawlController = getCrawlController(&quot;basic&quot;);
&gt;  &gt; waitFor(crawlController);
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; // Set up utility to wait for signal from crawler.
&gt;  &gt; JmxWaiter waiter = new JmxWaiter(server, crawlController, &quot;FINISHED&quot;);
&gt;  &gt; waiter.waitUntilNotification(0L);
&gt;  &gt; }
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; protected String createNewJob(final String jobName, final String[]
&gt;  &gt; urls, int pathDepth) throws Exception {
&gt;  &gt; final String CONTACT_URL = &quot;http://www.mycompany.com 
&gt; &lt;http://www.mycompany.com&gt;&quot;;
&gt;  &gt; final String CONTACT_EMAIL = &quot;yournam@...&quot;;
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; //-- job creation --
&gt;  &gt; String stateJobName = null;
&gt;  &gt; Object result = server.invoke(
&gt;  &gt; engine,
&gt;  &gt; &quot;listJobs&quot;,
&gt;  &gt; new Object[0],
&gt;  &gt; new String[0]
&gt;  &gt; );
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; final String[] resultAsStringArray = (String[]) result;
&gt;  &gt; boolean alreadyExists = false;
&gt;  &gt; lookup:
&gt;  &gt; for (String s : resultAsStringArray) {
&gt;  &gt; for (JobStage js : JobStage.values()) {
&gt;  &gt; if (s.equals(js.getPrefix() + jobName)) {
&gt;  &gt; alreadyExists = true;
&gt;  &gt; stateJobName = js.getPrefix() + jobName;
&gt;  &gt; break lookup;
&gt;  &gt; }
&gt;  &gt; }
&gt;  &gt; }
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; if (alreadyExists) {
&gt;  &gt; server.invoke(
&gt;  &gt; engine,
&gt;  &gt; &quot;deleteJob&quot;,
&gt;  &gt; new Object[]{stateJobName},
&gt;  &gt; new String[]{JAVA_LANG_STRING}
&gt;  &gt; );
&gt;  &gt; }
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; stateJobName = JobStage.READY.getPrefix() + jobName;
&gt;  &gt; server.invoke(
&gt;  &gt; engine,
&gt;  &gt; &quot;copy&quot;,
&gt;  &gt; new Object[]{&quot;profile-basic_seed_sites&quot;, stateJobName},
&gt;  &gt; new String[]{JAVA_LANG_STRING, JAVA_LANG_STRING}
&gt;  &gt; );
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; //-- job configuration --
&gt;  &gt; server.invoke(
&gt;  &gt; engine,
&gt;  &gt; &quot;getSheetManagerStub&quot;,
&gt;  &gt; new Object[]{stateJobName},
&gt;  &gt; new String[]{JAVA_LANG_STRING}
&gt;  &gt; );
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; ObjectName sheetManager = getSheetManager(jobName);
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; //---- seeds setup ----
&gt;  &gt; Object seedsFile = server.invoke(
&gt;  &gt; sheetManager,
&gt;  &gt; &quot;resolve&quot;,
&gt;  &gt; new Object[]{&quot;global&quot;, &quot;root:seeds:seedsfile&quot;},
&gt;  &gt; new String[]{JAVA_LANG_STRING, JAVA_LANG_STRING}
&gt;  &gt; );
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; String pathToFile = HERITRIX_HOME + &quot;/jobs/&quot; + stateJobName + &quot;/&quot; +
&gt;  &gt; seedsFile;
&gt;  &gt; File f = new File(pathToFile);
&gt;  &gt; if (f.exists() && f.isFile()) {
&gt;  &gt; FileWriter fw = new FileWriter(f);
&gt;  &gt; for (String url : urls) {
&gt;  &gt; fw.write(url);
&gt;  &gt; }
&gt;  &gt; fw.close();
&gt;  &gt; }
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; //---- other parameters ----
&gt;  &gt; server.invoke(
&gt;  &gt; sheetManager,
&gt;  &gt; &quot;checkout&quot;,
&gt;  &gt; new Object[]{&quot;global&quot;},
&gt;  &gt; new String[]{JAVA_LANG_STRING}
&gt;  &gt; );
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; //arguments to set: sheetName,path,type,value
&gt;  &gt; server.invoke(
&gt;  &gt; sheetManager,
&gt;  &gt; &quot;set&quot;,
&gt;  &gt; new Object[]{&quot;global&quot;, &quot;root:metadata:operator-contact-url&quot;,
&gt;  &gt; &quot;string&quot;, CONTACT_URL},
&gt;  &gt; new String[]{JAVA_LANG_STRING, JAVA_LANG_STRING, JAVA_LANG_STRING,
&gt;  &gt; JAVA_LANG_STRING}
&gt;  &gt; );
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; server.invoke(
&gt;  &gt; sheetManager,
&gt;  &gt; &quot;set&quot;,
&gt;  &gt; new Object[]{&quot;global&quot;, &quot;root:metadata:operator-from&quot;, &quot;string&quot;,
&gt;  &gt; CONTACT_EMAIL},
&gt;  &gt; new String[]{JAVA_LANG_STRING, JAVA_LANG_STRING, JAVA_LANG_STRING,
&gt;  &gt; JAVA_LANG_STRING}
&gt;  &gt; );
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; result = server.invoke(
&gt;  &gt; sheetManager,
&gt;  &gt; &quot;set&quot;,
&gt;  &gt; new Object[]{&quot;global&quot;, &quot;root:scope:rules:5:max-path-depth&quot;, &quot;int&quot;,
&gt;  &gt; ((Integer)pathDepth).toString()},
&gt;  &gt; new String[]{JAVA_LANG_STRING, JAVA_LANG_STRING, JAVA_LANG_STRING,
&gt;  &gt; JAVA_LANG_STRING}
&gt;  &gt; );
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; // server.invoke(
&gt;  &gt; // sheetManager,
&gt;  &gt; // &quot;set&quot;,
&gt;  &gt; // new Object[]{&quot;global&quot;, &quot;root:controller:processors:Archiver&quot;,
&gt;  &gt; &quot;object&quot;, &quot;org.archive.modules.writer.MirrorWriterProcessor2&quot;},
&gt;  &gt; // new String[]{JAVA_LANG_STRING, JAVA_LANG_STRING,
&gt;  &gt; JAVA_LANG_STRING, JAVA_LANG_STRING}
&gt;  &gt; // );
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; server.invoke(
&gt;  &gt; sheetManager,
&gt;  &gt; &quot;commit&quot;,
&gt;  &gt; new Object[]{&quot;global&quot;},
&gt;  &gt; new String[]{JAVA_LANG_STRING}
&gt;  &gt; );
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; return stateJobName;
&gt;  &gt; }
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; protected void createJobs() throws Exception {
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; final String jobName1 = &quot;newJob1&quot;;
&gt;  &gt; final String jobName2 = &quot;newJob2&quot;;
&gt;  &gt; final String[] job1Urls = {&quot;http://www.company.com 
&gt; &lt;http://www.company.com&gt;&quot;};
&gt;  &gt; final String[] job2Urls = {&quot;http://www.organisation.org 
&gt; &lt;http://www.organisation.org&gt;&quot;};
&gt;  &gt; final String stateJobName1 = createNewJob(jobName1, job1Urls, 3);
&gt;  &gt; final String stateJobName2 = createNewJob(jobName2, job2Urls, 3);
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; server.invoke(
&gt;  &gt; engine,
&gt;  &gt; &quot;launchJob&quot;,
&gt;  &gt; new Object[]{stateJobName1},
&gt;  &gt; new String[]{JAVA_LANG_STRING}
&gt;  &gt; );
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; // server.invoke(
&gt;  &gt; // engine,
&gt;  &gt; // &quot;launchJob&quot;,
&gt;  &gt; // new Object[]{stateJobName2},
&gt;  &gt; // new String[]{JAVA_LANG_STRING}
&gt;  &gt; // );
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; engine = null;
&gt;  &gt; server = null;
&gt;  &gt; }
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; protected static ObjectName getCrawlController(final String job)
&gt;  &gt; throws Exception {
&gt;  &gt; MBeanServer server = ManagementFactory.getPlatformMBeanServer();
&gt;  &gt; @SuppressWarnings(&quot;unchecked&quot;)
&gt;  &gt; Set&lt;ObjectName&gt; set = server.queryNames(null, null);
&gt;  &gt; for (ObjectName name : set) {
&gt;  &gt; if (name.getDomain().equals(&quot;org.archive.crawler&quot;)
&gt;  &gt; && name.getKeyProperty(&quot;name&quot;).equals(job)
&gt;  &gt; &&
&gt;  &gt;
&gt; name.getKeyProperty(&quot;type&quot;).equals(&quot;org.archive.crawler.framework.CrawlController&quot;))
&gt;  &gt; {
&gt;  &gt; return name;
&gt;  &gt; }
&gt;  &gt; }
&gt;  &gt; return null;
&gt;  &gt; }
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; protected static ObjectName getEngine() throws Exception {
&gt;  &gt; return waitFor(&quot;org.archive.crawler:*,name=Engine&quot;, true);
&gt;  &gt; }
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; protected ObjectName lazyGetEngine() throws Exception {
&gt;  &gt; if ( engine == null ) {
&gt;  &gt; return getEngine();
&gt;  &gt; } else {
&gt;  &gt; return engine;
&gt;  &gt; }
&gt;  &gt; }
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; protected static ObjectName getSheetManager(String jobName) throws
&gt;  &gt; Exception {
&gt;  &gt; return waitFor(&quot;org.archive.crawler:*,name=&quot; + jobName, true);
&gt;  &gt; }
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; //Utility method to check existence of MBean with matching name on
&gt; server
&gt;  &gt; protected static void waitFor(ObjectName name) throws Exception {
&gt;  &gt; final MBeanServer server = ManagementFactory.getPlatformMBeanServer();
&gt;  &gt; int count = 0;
&gt;  &gt; while (server.queryNames(name, null).isEmpty()) {
&gt;  &gt; count++;
&gt;  &gt; if (count &gt; 40) {
&gt;  &gt; throw new IllegalStateException(&quot;Could not find &quot; +
&gt;  &gt; name + &quot; after 20 seconds.&quot;);
&gt;  &gt; }
&gt;  &gt; Thread.sleep(500);
&gt;  &gt; }
&gt;  &gt; }
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; //Utility method to retrieve MBean matching query from server
&gt;  &gt; protected static ObjectName waitFor(final String query, final boolean
&gt;  &gt; exist) throws Exception {
&gt;  &gt; final MBeanServer server = ManagementFactory.getPlatformMBeanServer();
&gt;  &gt; final ObjectName name = new ObjectName(query);
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; Set set = server.queryNames(null, name);
&gt;  &gt; int count = 0;
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; while (set.isEmpty() == exist) {
&gt;  &gt; count++;
&gt;  &gt; if (count &gt; 40) {
&gt;  &gt; throw new IllegalStateException(&quot;Could not find &quot; +
&gt;  &gt; name + &quot; after 20 seconds.&quot;);
&gt;  &gt; }
&gt;  &gt; Thread.sleep(500);
&gt;  &gt; set = server.queryNames(null, name);
&gt;  &gt; if (set.size() &gt; 1) {
&gt;  &gt; throw new IllegalStateException(set.size() + &quot; matches for &quot; +
&gt; query);
&gt;  &gt; }
&gt;  &gt; }
&gt;  &gt; if (set.isEmpty()) {
&gt;  &gt; return null;
&gt;  &gt; } else {
&gt;  &gt; return (ObjectName) set.iterator().next();
&gt;  &gt; }
&gt;  &gt; }
&gt;  &gt; }
&gt;  &gt; --------------------------
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; You will want to make the following calls at some point :
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; this.startHeritrix();
&gt;  &gt; this.createJobs();
&gt;  &gt; this.stopHeritrix();
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; --- In archive-crawler@yahoogroups.com 
&gt; &lt;mailto:archive-crawler%40yahoogroups.com&gt;, Micah Wedemeyer &lt;mwedeme@&gt;
&gt;  &gt; wrote:
&gt;  &gt; &gt;
&gt;  &gt; &gt; Hi,
&gt;  &gt; &gt;
&gt;  &gt; &gt; I&#39;ve been playing around with 1.12, and I embedded it into another
&gt;  &gt; &gt; application. I am using the CrawlJobHandler in order to distance
&gt;  &gt; myself
&gt;  &gt; &gt; from the internals.
&gt;  &gt; &gt;
&gt;  &gt; &gt; Now, it looks like I&#39;ll have to provide a lot more
&gt; configurability, and
&gt;  &gt; &gt; that means tying in to heritrix a little more tightly. So, rather
&gt; than
&gt;  &gt; &gt; continue with 1.12, I decided to try and jump in with 2.0
&gt;  &gt; &gt;
&gt;  &gt; &gt; Anyways, if I want to treat heritrix as an API or a library for
&gt;  &gt; &gt; crawling, what&#39;s the procedure for setting everything up and
&gt;  &gt; executing a
&gt;  &gt; &gt; crawl? Here&#39;s the basic flow I want:
&gt;  &gt; &gt;
&gt;  &gt; &gt; 1) Configure settings (I assume this involves creating sheets)
&gt;  &gt; &gt; 2) Pass settings to heritrix
&gt;  &gt; &gt; 3) Start up heritrix
&gt;  &gt; &gt; 4) Periodically check status, and possibly send commands like pause
&gt;  &gt; or stop
&gt;  &gt; &gt;
&gt;  &gt; &gt; From what I&#39;ve seen in the javadocs, I&#39;m confused about where to
&gt;  &gt; start.
&gt;  &gt; &gt; Do I need to instantiate an Engine object? A CrawlController?
&gt;  &gt; How do
&gt;  &gt; &gt; I create the settings (sheets?) and pass them where they need to go?
&gt;  &gt; &gt;
&gt;  &gt; &gt; A few pointers on how to start would be great.
&gt;  &gt; &gt;
&gt;  &gt; &gt; Thanks,
&gt;  &gt; &gt; Micah Wedemeyer
&gt;  &gt; &gt;
&gt;  &gt;
&gt; 
&gt;
